<div class="quotetitle">infiniteneslives wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />I've got a copy of CV3, but it doesn't sound like that'll help with anything.  Let me know if tracing out some specific signals on there would help.<br /></div>Since none of the US MMC5 games populate the audio components, the maybe-amplifer between pins 1 and 100 is floating. Determining whether it's an inverter used as an amplifier would be nice, as well as figuring out what kind of gain it produces when biased with the R4's recommended 10kΩ resistor and fed with the 15kΩ/0.1µF highpass used for all the inputs.<br /><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />I have a copy of Just Breed, but what am I supposed to do exactly ?<br /></div>Most trivial thing to do would be touch an audio amplifier (or oscilloscope) to MMC5 pins 2 or 3 and see if you hear (see) the two pulse waves. To make it easier, those traces go to the bottom end of R2 and R1 respectively.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Mon Jan 20, 2014 4:00 pm</p><hr />
