Apparently I was wrong about thinking I couldn't see the <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/File:MMC5_audio.png" class="postlink">audio portion of the MMC5 PCB</a>. Can anyone with a MMC5 game that uses audio, or with an MMC5 game and a CopyNES, determine which signals are on pins 2 and 3? I suspect one's the pulse waves and the other's the DAC.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Mon Jan 20, 2014 2:22 pm</p><hr />
